1.title: Didgeridoo Hullabaloo
1.plot: Panzee is shocked to find out that Moaning Stones, Granite and Gravel, have never celebrated a birthday in all their many years. The ZingZillas decide to get them the perfect birthday gift but what do you get a standing stone that has everything?

2.title: Tang's Happy Day
2.plot: It's a beautiful sunny day on ZingZilla Island and Tang has written a happy song which is perfect for a hot sunny day - if only he could get anyone on the island to listen to it!

3.title: Rock Guitar
3.plot: Zak wants to play rock guitar but there isn't time to learn how to play before the Big Zing. Will the new broom DJ Loose gave him come to the rescue?

4.title: Auntie Dot's Dash
4.plot: Todd disguises himself as his Auntie Dot when she can't make it to the Big Zing. But will the ZingZillas discover his plan?

5.title: Scatzilla
5.plot: With help from Dame Cleo Laine and friends, Zak finds his voice just in time for the Big Zing.

6.title: Operatic Todd
6.plot: With the help of opera singer, Sarah Connolly, the ZingZillas discover that Todd also has a fantastic operatic voice, but only when he sings in the bath!

7.title: Sticker Trouble
7.plot: Panzee loves the sound of the cello and is thrilled when Julian Lloyd Webber agrees to play a duet with her in the Big Zing. She needs a lot of help from her friends though to play the piece perfectly.

8.title: Bhangra Beats
8.plot: Zak takes Tang and Panzee for a jog through the jungle but his shortcut back to the Clubhouse takes them all the way to the far side of ZingZilla Island. Will they make it back in time for the Bhangra Big Zing or will Drum have to do it on her own?

9.title: Squeaky Boots
9.plot: Panzee's new boots have arrived but they don't sound quite as nice as they look.

10.title: Sweet Dreams
10.plot: Drum is excited about staying up late. How can the ZingZillas persuade her to have a nap in the afternoon?
